Ketty Lester (born Revoyda Frierson; August 16, 1934) is an American singer and actress known for her 1962 hit single  "Love Letters", which reached the top 5 of the charts in the U.S. and the UK.
Ketty Lester was born Revoyda Frierson on August 16, 1934 in Hope, Arkansas.

Lester's recording of "Love Letters", which featured Lincoln Mayorga's sparse piano arrangement and Earl Palmer on drums, rose to #5 on the Billboard Hot 100 early in 1962.
